==English==
===Noun===
'''[[black]] [[vomit]]'''

# a blackish matter, resembling coffee grounds and due to hæmorrhage, vomited in severer cases of [[yellow fever]]; also, the disease of yellow fever itself
#:'''1833''' ''Cyclopædia of practical medicine'' II. 295&nbsp; A fever, with yellow skin and black vomit in some of the cases, appeared among a party of forty men.
#:'''1876''' John S. Bristowe ''A treatise on the theory and practice of medicine'' (1878) 199&nbsp; On the third or fourth day, or later, the vomited matters..begin to contain blood..and they soon assume..a coffee-ground character, constituting the so-called 'black vomit'.